Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}.

Place @Flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{}. (For 4, divide flatbreads between two sheets; toast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through.) Brush each flatbread all over with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon}. Toast on top rack until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian Chicken Sausage Mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat. Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer sausage to a paper-towel-lined plate.

Meanwhile, combine tomato, garlic, and a drizzle of olive oil in a #small bowl{}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @Arugula{2%ounce} with a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Heat broiler to high. Carefully spread toasted flatbreads with @Roasted Red Pepper Hummus{4%ounce}. Top with tomato and garlic. Broil until tomato and garlic are softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. (For 4 servings, broil in batches.)

Remove flatbreads from oven. Carefully sprinkle with @Mozzarella Cheese{½%cup}. Broil until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Sprinkle flatbreads with sausage along with mozzarella.

Allow flatbreads to cool slightly, then slice each into quarters. Top with arugula and drizzle with @Balsamic Glaze{5%teaspoon}. Serve.